  <prompt>
    Move the existing `useDocumentActions` hook from
    `src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/src/hooks/useDocumentActions.ts`
    into the new `@spaarke/document-operations` shared library (created by
    task 030). This is a VERBATIM move — the hook implementation does not
    change in this task; only its location and export path change. Task 032
    then refactors SemanticSearch's consumer to import from the shared lib.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer with expertise in TypeScript module refactoring,
    preserving public API surface while changing physical location.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `useDocumentActions` lives at
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DocumentOperations/src/hooks/useDocumentActions.ts`,
    is exported from the package barrel (`@spaarke/document-operations`),
    builds clean standalone, and the original SemanticSearch file is removed
    (or left as a thin re-export stub in this task, removed in task 032
    after consumers refactor).
  </goal>

