  <notes completed="2026-06-29">
    <summary>
      `useDocumentActions` moved from `src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/src/hooks/useDocumentActions.ts`
      to `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DocumentOperations/src/hooks/useDocumentActions.ts`.
      Original SemanticSearch file replaced with a thin shim that re-exports the
      canonical hook and binds SemanticSearch's local `getBffBaseUrl()` to the
      injected `bffBaseUrl` parameter — preserves the zero-arg call site for
      `SearchCommandBar.tsx` and other in-house consumers during the transition.
      Task 032 removes the shim after refactoring consumers.
    </summary>
    <design-decisions>
      <decision>
        Hook signature minimally changed from `useDocumentActions()` to
        `useDocumentActions({ bffBaseUrl })`. The original imported
        `getBffBaseUrl` from SemanticSearch's local `services/apiBase` path
        — that relative import cannot exist in the shared lib. Injecting
        `bffBaseUrl` as a parameter is the smallest possible change that
        decouples the hook from SemanticSearch internals without altering
        any of the six actions' fetch shapes or return contract.
      </decision>
      <decision>
        Kept the original SemanticSearch hook file as a thin re-export shim
        rather than deleting it now. Per POML step 4 option (a). This lets
        SemanticSearch's `SearchCommandBar.tsx` continue to call
        `useDocumentActions()` with zero args throughout the transition.
        Task 032 removes the shim and updates consumers to import
        `useDocumentActions` directly from `@spaarke/document-operations`.
      </decision>
      <decision>
        Added React deduplication (webpack alias + jest moduleNameMapper) to
        SemanticSearch — without it, the shared lib's local React 19 copy
        was being pulled in alongside SemanticSearch's, producing the
        classic "Invalid hook call" / `Cannot read properties of null
        (reading 'useState')` failure mode at runtime AND in jest.
      </decision>
    </design-decisions>
