    <test-results>
      Shared lib `@spaarke/document-operations`: 14 unit tests pass; 0 fail. Build clean (`npm run build` → tsc completes; `npm test` → 14/14 pass).
      SemanticSearch webpack build: clean (compiled with 3 pre-existing bundle-size warnings, 0 errors).
      SemanticSearch existing useDocumentActions.test.ts: 27 tests fail, BUT these tests fail on master too — pre-existing test debt (the test mocks `buildAuthHeaders` from `apiBase`, but the production hook never called `buildAuthHeaders` — it uses `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`). Task 032 should rewrite this test file against the canonical shared-lib hook.
    </test-results>
    <pre-existing-debt-uncovered>
      SemanticSearch's `src/__tests__/hooks/useDocumentActions.test.ts` was authored against an incorrect mock surface BEFORE this task. The production hook calls `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`, but the test mocks `buildAuthHeaders` + `global.fetch`. Pre-existing master state confirmed via git stash before-and-after run. Recommend deferring to task 032 (full SemanticSearch refactor) which rewrites the consumer's test against the shared-lib hook.
    </pre-existing-debt-uncovered>
